- Migration: PostgreSQL datasource configuration field user renamed to username; datasource payloads must be updated accordingly (#246)
- Add: make `datasourceId` optional when creating datasources, defaulting to "default" when not provided (#245)
- Add: configurable consistency refresh for window-based FDAs, scheduling periodic full rebuilds to recover delayed historical gaps while preserving incremental refreshes (new field consistencyRefreshInterval) (#231)
- Add: windowSize param in refresh policy now supports a custom amount before the unit (#219)
- Add: persist FDA schema in MongoDB during creation (strict mode) and use it for DA validation and default DA generation (#233)
- Add: introduce `validationMode` field (`strict` / `unchecked`) to control synchronous schema validation; `unchecked` skips validation and default DA creation, enabling fast FDA creation for heavy queries (#209, #222)
- Add: add `initFetch` timestamp to FDA document to track fetch cycle start time, alongside `lastFetch` for completion (#223)
- Fix: change DA creation response from 200 to 204 No Content, aligning with datasource creation behavior (#238)
- Fix: remove automatic timeColumn injection and add timeColumn validation (in `strict` mode) to prevent column duplication and ambiguous column errors in generated queries (#232)
- Fix: remove legacy `__schema__.parquet` fallback logic (#217)
- Fix: allow DA creation even when source table is empty or parquet files are missing, by validating against stored schema (strict) or skipping validation (unchecked) (#217, #222)
- Fix: first fetch in sliding window FDAs now uses windowSize, recurring fetches use fetchSize (#221)
- Fix: validate PostgreSQL FDA schemas at creation time and preserve typed schema metadata for empty partitioned FDA bootstrap, generating schema-only parquet fallback in MinIO and using it for DA validation/execution when partition files are absent (#217)
- Fix: reject DA definitions when query placeholders are not declared in params to prevent runtime bind errors and 500 responses (#225)
- Fix: removed agendaJobIds workaround after upgrading Agenda backend partial data filter support; recurring job cancellation is now scoped by name plus data service, fdaId and servicePath (#206)
